This <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">Indenture</ENAMEX>, Made the  <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Johnson</ENAMEX> and
in the ver-

of <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Calvin, Johnson</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.rel">deceased</ENAMEX>, of the first part, and the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">City of
Rochester</ENAMEX>, a <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Municipal Corporation</ENAMEX>
of the second part
Thitnesseth, That the said parties of the first part, in consideration of the sum of
<NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">One
Dollars</NUMEX>
lawful money of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">United States</ENAMEX> paid by the party of the second part, do hereby grant and release unto the said party of the
second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX> forever,
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Il</ENAMEX> that Tract of <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Marcel</ENAMEX> of Land situate in the own of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Livonia</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Livingston</ENAMEX>
and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>, being part of Lot No. 66 in the original survey
and bounded and described as follows.
Beginning at a point on the West share of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE.notgpe">Hombock
Lake</ENAMEX>, at highwater mark a little South of a black
<ENAMEX TYPE="FLORA">walnut</ENAMEX> tree, and running thence south along the
share of said bake <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">100</NUMEX> feet to the corner of a Lot
deeded by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Russell R. Jacques</ENAMEX> to <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Beadle</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">Brothers</ENAMEX> by
deed dated <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">August 12, 1879</TIMEX> and recorded in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Livingston
County</ENAMEX> in <ENAMEX TYPE="WORK_OF_ART">Lib. 1100 of Deeds</ENAMEX> page 443.
Thence westerly along said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Beadle Brothers</ENAMEX> worth
line to a stake at <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> northwest corner in the center
of a roadway about <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">two hundred and ten ( 210)</NUMEX> feet,
t Thence North <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">20th</NUMEX> degrees east along the center of said
roadway <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">100</NUMEX> feet to a stake.
Thence easterly to the place of beginning, containing
<NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">about a half</NUMEX> an acre of land, be the same more or less:
1 8
Excepting thereout all that portion there of that lies
west of a line <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">two hundred</NUMEX> feet west of and parallel
to highwater mark on the share of said Lake.
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Alice</ENAMEX>
All that other tract or parcel of land lying in said
town on the west share of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE.notgpe">Hemlock Lake</ENAMEX> and bounded
and described as follows.
Being <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">forty seven ( 47)</NUMEX> feet in width off from the northerly side of tract or parcel of land conveyed by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Russell R.</ENAMEX>
 <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">R.</ENAMEX>
facques, to said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">William W. Beadle</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Thomas S. Beadle</ENAMEX>,
and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">George Beadle</ENAMEX> by deed dated <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">August 12. 1879</TIMEX>,
described as follows: viz:-
Beginning at a stake and stones on the west share of
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE.notgpe">H Anback Lake</ENAMEX> at the Northeast corner of a Lot deeded by
said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Beadle</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">brothers</ENAMEX> to <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Roscoe B. Ashley</ENAMEX>, and running
thence North <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">142</NUMEX> degrees east <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">one</NUMEX> chain and <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">63 </NUMEX> links
along the share of said Lake to a stake.

to a stake and stones in the center of a roadway.

along the center of said road to the center of a Carine   
or gally. Thence eastwardly along the center of said fully
to the place of beginning, containing <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">about 5/100</NUMEX> of and
acre of land be the same more or less.

feet west of and parallel to high water mark on the west
share of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE.notgpe">Hemlock Lake</ENAMEX>.

at <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">4 th clock A. M.</TIMEX>
